<subSubSection pageId="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,895,1317]" pageId="2">Dark brown (Plate I: D). Head broader than pronotum. Vertex black with yellowish posterior margin, a pair of yellowish spots at anterior margin. Ocelli at anterior margin next to eyes. Pronotum and scutellum with shiny black appearance. Eyes grey to silvery. Forewing macropterous with brown veins. Frontoclypeus mostly black, anteclypeus black with lateral yellow spots (Plate I: F).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,895,1317]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1076,1101]" pageId="2">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with darkly sclerotized part on posteroventral margin less than its half, with sparse spinules, dorsoapical margin with macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[689,790,1111,1136]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1087,1109]" captionTargetBox="[252,1335,204,1055]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[244,1345,193,1075]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aconurella erebus (Distant). A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242511/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: A). Pair of spinular bunches present near the anal tube base. Connective Y-shaped with arms close together distally (
<figureCitation box="[848,948,1148,1173]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1087,1109]" captionTargetBox="[252,1335,204,1055]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[244,1345,193,1075]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aconurella erebus (Distant). A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242511/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: C). Subgenital plate with 5–6 macrosetae, longer than pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[389,489,1183,1208]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1087,1109]" captionTargetBox="[252,1335,204,1055]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[244,1345,193,1075]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aconurella erebus (Distant). A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242511/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: B). Style with well developed claw-like apophysis, inner process longer than outer process, wide apart (
<figureCitation box="[381,480,1220,1245]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1087,1109]" captionTargetBox="[252,1335,204,1055]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[244,1345,193,1075]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aconurella erebus (Distant). A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242511/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: D). Aedeagus slightly expanded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[952,1051,1220,1245]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1087,1109]" captionTargetBox="[252,1335,204,1055]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[244,1345,193,1075]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aconurella erebus (Distant). A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242511/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: E–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
